title: Lamamra received by Iraqi Prime Minister Mustafa Al-Kadhimi
text: As part of his working visit to Baghdad, Special Envoy of President of Republic Abdelmadjid Tebboune, Minister of Foreign Affairs and National Community Abroad Ramtane Lamamra was received on Saturday afternoon at the Government Palace by Iraqi Prime Minister, General Commander of the Iraqi Armed Forces Mustafa Al-Kadhimi, to whom he handed a message of brotherhood and cooperation sent by President of the Republic Abdelmadjid Tebboune to the Iraqi leaders.

The meeting allowed the two parties to affirm their determination to intensify efforts to promote bilateral relations in various fields, in accordance with practical steps and a timetable aimed at activating bilateral cooperation mechanisms, headed by the Algerian-Iraqi joint commission, whose 14thÂ session will be held at the end of November in Algiers.

It was also agreed to strengthen consultations and coordination between the two countries, through the intensification of the exchange of visits at the highest level to consolidate the convergence of positions of the two countries on all regional and international issues, through their common commitments and references.
